  "title": "Related rates with area of triangle",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p>If the base <em>b</em> of a triangle is increasing at a rate of 3 inches per minute while its height <em>h</em> is\ndecreasing at a rate of 3 inches per minute, which of the following must be true about the area <em>A</em> of the triangle? </p>",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "value": "i0",
        "label": "<p>  <em>A</em> is always increasing. </p>"
      },
      {
        "value": "i1",
        "label": "<p>  <em>A</em> is always decreasing. </p>"
      },
      {
        "value": "i2",
        "label": "<p>  <em>A</em> is decreasing only when <em>b&lt;h</em>.</p>"
      },
      {
        "value": "i3",
        "label": "<p> <em>A</em> is decreasing only when <em>b&gt;h</em>.</p>"
      },
      {
        "value": "i4",
        "label": "<p>A remains constant. </p>"
      }
    ]
  },
